# Compiled class files — this is almost certainly why your repo files showed
# a coffee-cup icon and appeared "empty" on GitHub: .class files are binary
# bytecode, not text, so GitHub can't render a preview for them, and if the
# copy/commit was interrupted or done over a flaky connection they can easily
# end up truncated to 0 bytes. Only source (.java) and build config should
# ever be committed — never the out/ or target/ build output.
*.class
out/
target/
bin/

# IDE metadata
.idea/
*.iml
*.ipr
*.iws
.vscode/
.settings/
.classpath
.project

# OS files
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Logs
*.log
